title: An Antarctic Mystery or The Sphinx of the Ice Fields
creator: Jules Verne
description: Librivox recording of An Antarctic Mystery or The Sphinx of the Ice Fields by Jules Verne read by Esther. Edgar Allan Poe’s telling of Arthur Pym’s narrative is shown to be true as events come together that bring out clues that help Captain Len Guy trace the fate of his brother’s ship the Jane; the very ship that Arthur Pym was on board at the time of his disappearance. Through the efforts of Mr. Joerling, the crew of the Halbrane is enticed to make the trip to Antarctica to search for any survivors of the Jane. Summary from Wikipedia For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audiobooks or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org M4B audiobook of complete book
subject: librivox; audiobook; adventure; shipwreck
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I love this book and the reading.  It is so amazing how Verne interlaces Poe's original story into his own---and expands it.  Very clever.  You really have to listen carefully to get all the details, but it is well worth it. I give this book---and the reader---ten stars.
This was a great book(thank you, Jules Verne) and the reading was great:) Both get top marks:P
